The paper presents a new dynamic data structure for maintaining strongly connected components and dominator trees in directed graphs under edge deletions. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also involves computational geometry (cs.CG) in the sense that it deals with connectivity queries in graphs. Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds (cs.DL) for the running time of the algorithms presented. Overall, the most likely categories are cs.DS and cs.DM, followed by cs.CG, cs.LG (for the graph theory aspect), and cs.DL.
